						<!-- Two -->
							<section id="two">
								<div class="container">
									<h3>Facia - What is it?</h3>
									<p>Fascia is a connective tissue that weave around nerves, muscles, blood vessels, and bones in a three dimensional web, without interruption throughout your body.  This tissue provides support, shock absorption, and creates space between structures.  When faced with trauma, poor posture, inflammatory process, or a combination of any of these, the fascia will have a tendency to shorten and bind, causing excessive pressure on structures, creating pain and loss of motion.  These fascial restrictions can be acute or develop over time.</p>
								</div>
							</section>

						<!-- Three -->
							<section id="three">
								<div class="container">
									<h3>Myofascial Release  - What’s it all about?</h3>
									<p>Myofascial release is a hands on technique, using gentle sustained pressure, stretching, and/or compression, performed on direct contact with skin.  The focus is to release these fascial restrictions that develop in the connective tissue so the client may improve movement and postural alignment, as well as function within a pain free environment.  The more frequent treatments that clients are able to participate with, the better the outcome to reaching painfree potential.   The myofascial techniques used at Connective Release, LLC utilizes techniques from the John Barnes’ Myofascial Release Therapy.  If you would like further information regarding John Barnes’ Myofascial Release, please refer to this link:  https://www.myofascialrelease.com</p>
									
								</div>
							</section>
							
